1. What are the big differences between cookies and local storage?
    Cookies interact with the server, while local storage does not. Local storage also
    stores more data than a cookie.
2. Why would you use a cookie instead of local storage?
    If you need to interact with the server at all to access information, cookies are the only form of borwser storage that can do so.
3. Why would you use local storage instead of a cookie?
    If you need to store more data, and do not want to interact with the server at all to save time.
4. What are the limitations of both options?
    They both are limited storage options, and are much lower security than using something like a data server.
